<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="534" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/11045:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-17T19:00:00+01:00">June 17,
                                    1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 17—3:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2185. Department’s 1206, June 16, 3 p.m. Swedish Government has informed
                            Germans that all transit shipments of goods to either Norway or Finland
                            via Bothnian route must cease by August 1.</p>
                        <p>My 590, June 17, 7 p.m. repeats this to London with reference to my 462,
                            May 24, midnight.<note n="84" xml:id="d534fn1">Same as telegram 1856,
                                    <ref target="#pg_553">p. 553</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>